import pandas as pd  # pandas
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
from sklearn.cluster import DBSCAN

#1.
data = pd.read_excel('data.xlsx')
#2.
plt.scatter(data.iloc[:, 0], data.iloc[:, 1], c="green", marker='*') 
plt.xlabel('x') 
plt.ylabel('y')

Text(0, 0.5, 'y')
In [27]:
#3.
#dbs = DBSCAN()   #dbs = DBSCAN(eps=0.5, min_samples=3)


rs= []#
eps = np.arange(0.2,0.7,0.2) #eps0.210.2
min_samples=np.arange(2,6,1)#min_samples26
for i in eps:
    for j in min_samples:
        db=DBSCAN(eps=i, min_samples=j).fit(data)
        print(db)
        label_dbs = db.labels_
        print(label_dbs)
        plt.scatter(data[label_dbs == 0].iloc[:, 0], data[label_dbs == 0].iloc[:, 1], c="red", marker='o', label='class0') 
        plt.scatter(data[label_dbs == 1].iloc[:, 0], data[label_dbs == 1].iloc[:, 1], c="green", marker='*', label='class1')
        plt.scatter(data[label_dbs == 2].iloc[:, 0], data[label_dbs == 2].iloc[:, 1], c="blue", marker='*', label='class2')
        plt.scatter(data[label_dbs == 3].iloc[:, 0], data[label_dbs == 3].iloc[:, 1], c="yellow", marker='+', label='class3')
        plt.xlabel('x')
        plt.ylabel('y')
        plt.legend()
        plt.show()

#Pythonmatplotlibpyplot,.
#data.iloc[:, 0]xdata.iloc[:, 1]ycmarker
plt.scatter(data.iloc[:, 0], data.iloc[:, 1], c="green", marker='*') 
plt.xlabel('x')   #xy'x''y'
plt.ylabel('y') 

#
n_clusters_values=[2,3,4,5,6]
random_state_values=[0,10]

for i in n_clusters_values:
    for j in random_state_values:
        #3.
        kms = KMeans(n_clusters=i, random_state=j)    # KMeansn_clustersirandom_statej
        kms.fit(data)     # 
        label_kms = kms.labels_    # 
        #4.
        print(kms)
        print(label_kms)
        plt.scatter(data[label_kms == 0].iloc[:, 0], data[label_kms == 0].iloc[:, 1], c="red", marker='o', label='class0') #0
        plt.scatter(data[label_kms == 1].iloc[:, 0], data[label_kms== 1].iloc[:, 1], c="green", marker='*', label='class1')#1
        plt.scatter(data[label_kms == 2].iloc[:, 0], data[label_kms == 2].iloc[:, 1], c="blue", marker='o', label='class2') #2
        plt.scatter(data[label_kms == 3].iloc[:, 0], data[label_kms== 3].iloc[:, 1], c="yellow", marker='*', label='class3')#3
        plt.scatter(data[label_kms == 4].iloc[:, 0], data[label_kms== 4].iloc[:, 1], c="black", marker='*', label='class4')#4
        plt.scatter(data[label_kms == 5].iloc[:, 0], data[label_kms== 5].iloc[:, 1], c="orange", marker='o', label='class5')#5
         #xy'x''y'
        plt.xlabel('x')
        plt.ylabel('y')
        #plt.legend
        plt.legend() 
        plt.show()

In [20]:
# SSE
sse = []
for k in range(1, 11):
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=k, init='k-means++', max_iter=100, n_init=10, random_state=0)
    kmeans.fit(data)
    print(kmeans)
    sse.append(kmeans.inertia_)
    print(sse)
